  "text": "Every business cycle is driven by different factors, the refore a few approaches towards explaining this theory may be found in economic literature. One of such approaches deals with a real business cycle. According to [CITATION_1] , the theory of a real business cycle focuses on technological shocks or other disturbances on the supply side which are identified to be the main causes for fluctuations in the development of a country's economy. However, this business cycle model disregards shifts of the economy related to financial, political or social factors. In other words, this theory takes account of more natural volatilities of the eco nomy. The present article will not analyse real business cycle theory further due to a rather narrow viewpoint followed with regard to economic fluctuations.",
